ic, Persian and other languages, to study the individuals who produced our manuscripts and how they shaped the transmission of literary texts they copied.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aManuscriptszMiddle EastxEditing. 0aMarginaliazMiddle EastxHistory. 0aMiddle Eastern literaturexCriticism, Textual. 0aParatextzMiddle EastxHistory. 0aScribeszMiddle EastxHistory. 0aTransmission of textszMiddle EastxHistory. 4aAncient Languages. 4aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY. 4aGeneral. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Ancient Languages (see also Latin).2bisacsh1 aBuchanan, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Block, Fien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGažákovà, Zuzana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGürbüzel, Aslihan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatzoff, Binyamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiraz, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKrawczyk, Aryeh M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoopstra, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartín-Contreras, Elvira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMihan, Shiva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPragt, Marion, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, T. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidtke, Sabine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSövegjártó, Szilvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurnbull, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/